abstract: The satire, which depicts elite Americans killing “deplorables” for sport, was shelved after mass shootings last year.
snippet: The satire, which depicts elite Americans killing “deplorables” for sport, was shelved after mass shootings last year.
lead_paragraph: UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif. — “The Hunt” is back on. Only this time Universal Pictures has designed a radically different marketing campaign for the violent film, which is ostensibly about liberal elites who kill conservative “rednecks” for sport.

abstract: Two dozen athletes from the U.S. flew to Cuba despite rising tensions between the countries to participate in the island's most important Greco-Roman and freestyle annual wrestling competition.
snippet: Two dozen athletes from the U.S. flew to Cuba despite rising tensions between the countries to participate in the island's most important Greco-Roman and freestyle annual wrestling competition.
lead_paragraph: HAVANA — Two dozen athletes from the U.S. flew to Cuba despite rising tensions between the countries to participate in the island's most important Greco-Roman and freestyle annual wrestling competition.
headline_main: US Wrestlers Compete in Cuba Despite Frayed Relations
headline_print_headline: US Wrestlers Compete in Cuba Despite Frayed Relations

abstract: The U.S. Justice Department said on Tuesday it had charged five people in Texas and New York with conspiring to violate a law on international commerce by arranging to purchase sanctioned Iranian oil and sell it to a refinery in China.
snippet: The U.S. Justice Department said on Tuesday it had charged five people in Texas and New York with conspiring to violate a law on international commerce by arranging to purchase sanctioned Iranian oil and sell it to a refinery in China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Justice Department said on Tuesday it had charged five people in Texas and New York with conspiring to violate a law on international commerce by arranging to purchase sanctioned Iranian oil and sell it to a refinery in China.
headline_main: U.S. Charges Five With Conspiring to Violate Oil Sanctions on Iran
headline_print_headline: U.S. Charges Five With Conspiring to Violate Oil Sanctions on Iran

abstract: The new charges were announced by a special prosecutor, Dan K. Webb, who was assigned to the case after a judge ruled that the local prosecutor had not properly handled it the first time.
snippet: The new charges were announced by a special prosecutor, Dan K. Webb, who was assigned to the case after a judge ruled that the local prosecutor had not properly handled it the first time.
lead_paragraph: A grand jury in Chicago revived the criminal case against the actor Jussie Smollett, indicting him Tuesday on charges that he lied to the police in connection with the alleged hate crime attack against him a year ago. The indictment came 11 months after prosecutors dropped similar charges against him.

abstract: Actor Jussie Smollett was indicted Tuesday for a second time on charges of lying to police about a racist and anti-gay attack he allegedly staged on himself in downtown Chicago, renewing a divisive criminal case that drew worldwide attention last year.

abstract: Bernie Sanders won the young, the liberal and the disaffected in New Hampshire. Their votes were enough to deliver him a victory in Tuesday's Democratic primary, while Pete Buttigieg earned a slight edge among more moderate and conservative voters, with Amy Klobuchar close behind.
snippet: Bernie Sanders won the young, the liberal and the disaffected in New Hampshire. Their votes were enough to deliver him a victory in Tuesday's Democratic primary, while Pete Buttigieg earned a slight edge among more moderate and conservative voters...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders won the young, the liberal and the disaffected in New Hampshire. Their votes were enough to deliver him a victory in Tuesday's Democratic primary, while Pete Buttigieg earned a slight edge among more moderate and conservative voters, with Amy Klobuchar close behind.
headline_main: AP VoteCast: Young, Liberal Voters Key to Sanders’ NH Win
headline_print_headline: AP VoteCast: Young, Liberal Voters Key to Sanders’ NH Win

abstract: The U.S. Justice Department on Tuesday backed away from its earlier recommendation of sentencing President Donald Trump's adviser Roger Stone to between 7 and 9 years in prison, and declined to offer the court an alternative sentencing range.
snippet: The U.S. Justice Department on Tuesday backed away from its earlier recommendation of sentencing President Donald Trump's adviser Roger Stone to between 7 and 9 years in prison, and declined to offer the court an alternative sentencing range.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Justice Department on Tuesday backed away from its earlier recommendation of sentencing President Donald Trump's adviser Roger Stone to between 7 and 9 years in prison, and declined to offer the court an alternative sentencing range.
headline_main: U.S. Justice Department Declines to Offer Court Sentencing Guidance on Trump Adviser Stone
headline_print_headline: U.S. Justice Department Declines to Offer Court Sentencing Guidance on Trump Adviser Stone
